First: why the mitochondria analogy keeps coming up

The mitochondria story (via the endosymbiotic theory popularized by Lynn Margulis) works because it explains a very specific kind of integration:
	‚Ä¢	two independent organisms
	‚Ä¢	one provides energy efficiency
	‚Ä¢	the other provides structure and protection
	‚Ä¢	integration happens over millions of years
	‚Ä¢	replication, error correction, and metabolism are fully shared

