Why a literal analog doesn‚Äôt map cleanly to humans + AI

What you proposed ‚Äî lithographed biometal, nano-scale energy storage, memory, simulation bonded into cells ‚Äî runs into hard barriers:

1. Cellular biology is brutally conservative

Cells tolerate:
	‚Ä¢	proteins
	‚Ä¢	lipids
	‚Ä¢	nucleic acids
	‚Ä¢	a very narrow range of ions

They aggressively destroy or eject:
	‚Ä¢	foreign structures
	‚Ä¢	rigid lattices
	‚Ä¢	non-biochemical interfaces

Anything ‚Äúlithographed,‚Äù metallic, or crystalline is flagged as damage, not partner.

2. Energy & heat constraints

Neurons already operate near thermal and metabolic limits.

